If you have the time, it would be really helpful to me if you left a review from the place where you bought the book 🙏🏼 Thank you!

🚫THIS IS NOT ME 🚫
Just a reminder this scam account is still active. I’ve been made aware this morning that these scammers are not only approaching people to get you to purchase readings but are also trying to sell jewellery and asking you to donate money in my name.

This is a complete scam and I wanted you to be aware so you can spread the word so people don’t fall for their new tricks.

I’m just sorry I have to keep reposting the same kind of posts so much, but I would really hate to think that anyone would get scammed by this scum.

Lindsay 💜

node.text:
Social media can be an amazing way to connect with other Witches, Pagans and Wiccans from around the globe. It can help us feel less alone, especially if you are at the of your Witchcraft journey.

But social media can also be overwhelming too, particularly at the start. You might see other witches share things you’re not comfortable with sharing and wonder if there’s some sort of unwritten rule you have to bare these parts of your craft for all to see.

But you don’t! There are no rules except this - only post what you are happy and comfortable to share, regardless of what other people post on their accounts. 

Do what feels right for you! What is right for one doesn’t necessarily mean it feels right to you!

Lindsay 💜

node.text:
We are coming up to such a busy period!

We’ve got the Full Moon in Pisces and Mabon/Autumn Equinox on 21 September and the start of Libra season on 22 September. For those in the Southern Hemisphere, you’ll be getting ready to celebrate Ostara. Then a few days later on 26 September, we have the beginning of Mercury Retrograde.

I’ve got lots of new posts planned focusing on all these events, including correspondence, tarot spreads and rituals. As we get closer, I’ll start to post them.

I can really feel the change in the air start to come as we get closer to Mabon, the mornings are much cooler and I’m watching the leaves on rowan tree in my garden slowly turn golden brown.

Can you feel it where you are?

Lindsay 💜

node.text:
✨𝕋𝕒𝕣𝕠𝕥 ℝ𝕖𝕧𝕖𝕒𝕝 ✨ 
1. The reversed Sun can be a sign that you’ve been working hard lately and as a result, you’re feeling burnt out. It’s ok to rest when you need to, even if this is not something you find naturally easy to do. It’s ok to take some down time to look after your own sense of well-being, in fact, it’s necessary. Looking after yourself is important and is something you find quite difficult. Slowing down for a time rather than ploughing ahead in the way others expect you to is very liberating. It’s a reminder that sometimes, taking a more carefree approach is just what you need. Give yourself the permission to break the rigidity of the the adult world to look at life from a more child-like perspective.

2. The reversed Ace of Swords is often an indicator of an inner breakthrough or idea, but be cautious about sharing details with others until you’ve had the time to clear your mind first. You need to have a clear plan about what you want to do, how you want to do it as well as what this inner change means to you. The most important question you must ask yourself is will your idea or breakthrough bring you closer to the things you want most? If the answer is ‘yes’ then explore how best to manifest this in the external world in the most effective way. If the answer is ‘no’ then don’t be scared to go back to the drawing board and rethink things through.

3. The Nine of Cups is often known as the wish card as it’s an excellent omen that the things you’re working towards will soon come to fruition. Keep using your intentions to work towards your goal. Remember that what you put into the Universe, you receive, so keep a positive approach and this energy will be returned to you through success and fulfilment. This card is also a reminder to count your blessings and be consciously grateful for the people in your life. Overtime, this will help to intensify feelings of contentment as well as your ability to attract what you wish for. You attract what you give.

I love this photograph, it’s so captivating! It’s made even more so because I don’t know its history. I think it’s probably one of those photos from the Edwardian era, where people would dress up in a range of different costumes and pose as other people or characters just for fun.

It doesn’t really matter that the women were not likely to be real witches, it’s still a cool photo and a piece of history.

What do you think?

Lindsay 💜

✨ P𝕣𝕒𝕔𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕒𝕝 W𝕚𝕥𝕔𝕙𝕔𝕣𝕒𝕗𝕥 T𝕚𝕡𝕤✨
Egg shells have so many magickal uses, but before they are used, make sure they have been cleansed and the inner membrane removed so the shells are hygienic.

There are two ways to dry the shells, you can let them simply air dry, or if you need them faster, place them on a baking tray covered and bake at the lowest temperature your oven will go on for 10 minutes.

Does anyone know a good vegan alternative to egg shells? Someone once told me that sea shells and even nuts can be used 🤷🏼‍♀️

Lindsay 💜
